	(text_box "The temperature and EC probes share an isolated\npower supply and ADC, since the AMC3336 is expensive\nand takes a bunch of space.  This lets us be a\nlittle more space-efficient on the board,\nsince AMC3336's and their supporting passives\ntake up a bunch of space.\nThis circuit receives 2 isolated digital signals, \"Select\" and \"Square Wave\".\n- \"Select (SEL)\" toggles the active sensor between temperature and EC.\n- \"Square Wave (SQW)\" provides the AC excitation to the EC probe when it's measuring.\n\nThis is complicated by the need for each sensor to be high-Z when the other is measuring.\nSo, we use the 2 digital signals to route probe inputs and outputs as follows:\n|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| SEL | SQW | EC IN   | EC BOTTOM | TEMP IN | TEMP BOTTOM | ADC Reading |\n|-----|-------|---------|---------------|--------------------------------------------|\n|  0  |  0  |   GND   |    GND    |   GND   |     GND     | Temperature |\n|  0  |  1  |  High-Z |   High-Z  |   1V    |     GND     | Temperature |\n|  1  |  0  |   GND   |    1V     |  High-Z |   High-Z    |      EC     |\n|  1  |  1  |   1V    |    GND    |  High-Z |   High-Z    |      EC     |\n|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -76.835 55.88 0)
		(size 73.66 46.355)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Ebrima")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "38636a50-b254-4a6c-9204-4ddc66c0693c")
	)
